### 5.3.3 Sequence Diagram — AI Diagnostic Imaging Flow

The following sequence diagram describes the end-to-end flow of the AI-powered chest X-ray analysis:

**Actors/Components:** Patient (P), React Frontend (F), Express Backend (B), FastAPI AI Service (AI), Gemini API (G), MongoDB (DB)

```
P → F    : Uploads X-ray image + enters clinical data (age, sex, vitals, symptoms)
F → B    : POST /api/vision/analyze-v2 [multipart: image + clinical_data JSON]
B → B    : Multer parses file, extracts image buffer and clinical JSON
B → AI   : POST /api/vision/analyze [FormData: image file + clinical_data string]
AI → AI  : Preprocess image: Resize 224×224, Normalize (ImageNet μ,σ), ToTensor
AI → AI  : Preprocess clinical data: 15-dim vector (normalize age, vitals, binary symptoms)
AI → AI  : DenseNet-121 forward pass → logits_d, register Grad-CAM hooks
AI → AI  : Sigmoid(logits_d / τ) → probs_d (14 classes)
AI → AI  : ResNet-50 forward pass → logits_r
AI → AI  : Sigmoid(logits_r / τ) → probs_r (14 classes)
AI → G   : Send image + clinical vitals prompt to Gemini 2.5 Flash
G → AI   : Return 2-3 sentence clinical interpretation
AI → AI  : Ensemble: probs_max = elementwise_max(probs_d, probs_r)
AI → AI  : Compute Grad-CAM heatmap on DenseNet (backward pass on top class)
AI → AI  : Compute risk score (severity-weighted aggregation → 1-10 scale)
AI → AI  : Classify findings: high_priority / secondary / evaluated_negative
AI → AI  : Generate base64 heatmap overlay (JET colormap, 40:60 blend)
AI → B   : JSON response: {status, primary_flag, findings, risk_score, heatmap, consensus_panel}
B → F    : JSON response wrapped in {message, data}
F → P    : Render triage dashboard: heatmap, findings table, risk gauge, consensus panel
P → F    : Clicks "Save Report"
F → B    : POST /api/vision/save-report [report data]
B → DB   : Save ImagingReport document
DB → B   : Confirm save with report ID
B → F    : {message: "Report saved", report}
F → P    : Display confirmation toast
```

### 5.3.4 Sequence Diagram — Graph-RAG Patient Chat Flow

**Actors/Components:** Patient (P), React Frontend (F), Express Backend (B), FastAPI AI Service (AI), Neo4j (N4J), Sentence-BERT (SBERT), Groq LLM (LLM)

```
--- Phase 1: Report Ingestion ---
P → F     : Uploads PDF clinical report
F → AI    : POST /api/ingest-patient-report [file + patient_id]
AI → AI   : PyPDF2 extracts text from PDF
AI → LLM  : Send extracted text (first 1500 chars) for disease entity extraction
LLM → AI  : Return extracted disease name
AI → AI   : RecursiveCharacterTextSplitter: chunk text (300 chars, 50 overlap)
AI → SBERT: Encode each chunk → 384-dim embedding
SBERT → AI: Return embedding vectors
AI → N4J  : For each chunk: MERGE Patient, MERGE Disease, CREATE DiagnosisEvent
            SET event.embedding, event.clinical_notes
            MERGE (Patient)-[:HAS_DIAGNOSIS]->(event)-[:FOR_DISEASE]->(Disease)
N4J → AI  : Confirm graph write
AI → F    : {success: true, extracted_condition: "..."}
F → P     : Display "Report ingested" confirmation

--- Phase 2: Query & Retrieval ---
P → F     : Types medical question
F → B     : POST /api/chats/save [chatId, messages]
B → AI    : POST /api/graph-chat {question, patient_id}
AI → AI   : Augment query: prepend "Patient medical history..." keywords
AI → SBERT: Encode augmented query → 384-dim embedding
SBERT → AI: Return query vector
AI → N4J  : Vector search: queryNodes('diagnosis_embeddings', 10, embedding)
            MATCH (p:Patient {id: patient_id})-[:HAS_DIAGNOSIS]->(event)
            Filter: score >= 0.70
N4J → AI  : Return matching DiagnosisEvent nodes with scores
AI → AI   : Format retrieved context (disease, clinical_notes)
AI → LLM  : System prompt + patient context + user question
LLM → AI  : Generated clinical response
AI → B    : {reply: "...", sources: [...]}
B → F     : Save chat to MongoDB, return response
F → P     : Display AI response with source citations
```

