**Additional Route Modules:** `/api/medicines/` (CRUD), `/api/orders/` (order management), `/api/labs/` (lab operations), `/api/lab-tests/` (test catalog), `/api/users/` (profile management), `/api/prescriptions/` (prescription CRUD), `/api/reports/` (clinical report management).

### 6.1.3 AI Service Implementation

The FastAPI application (`main.py`, 385 lines) initializes at startup by:

1. Loading environment variables (Gemini API key, Neo4j credentials, Groq API key)
2. Initializing Neo4j driver and performing factory reset (development mode)
3. Loading Sentence-BERT model (all-MiniLM-L6-v2) for embedding generation
4. Initializing Groq client for Llama 3.1-8B chat completions
5. Loading DenseNet-121 and ResNet-50 ensemble models into GPU/MPS memory
6. Configuring CORS middleware

**API Endpoints:**

| Method | Endpoint | Lines | Description |
|--------|----------|-------|-------------|
| POST | `/api/vision/analyze` | 183–210 | Full multimodal chest X-ray analysis pipeline |
| POST | `/api/chat` | 212–259 | Doctor co-pilot chatbot with clinical context |
| POST | `/api/chat-title` | 262–268 | Auto-generate concise chat titles |
| POST | `/api/graph-chat` | 270–317 | Graph-RAG patient-specific query answering |
| POST | `/api/ingest-patient-report` | 320–385 | PDF ingestion into Neo4j knowledge graph |

**Predict Multimodal Pipeline (`predict_multimodal.py`, 335 lines):**

The core inference function `predict_multimodal()` executes the following operations:

1. Image preprocessing: Resize to 224×224, normalize with ImageNet statistics, convert to tensor
2. Clinical data preprocessing: 15-dimension feature vector with domain-specific normalization
3. DenseNet-121 forward pass with Grad-CAM hook registration
4. ResNet-50 forward pass (no gradient tracking required)
5. Gemini Vision API call with structured clinical prompt
6. Max-confidence ensemble aggregation
7. Grad-CAM backward pass, gradient pooling, heatmap generation
8. Heatmap colorization (JET), alpha blending (0.4:0.6), base64 encoding
9. Risk score computation with severity-weighted aggregation
10. Findings categorization and payload construction

### 6.1.4 Database Implementation

MongoDB contains fourteen document collections corresponding to the Mongoose schemas:

| Collection | Schema File | Key Fields |
|-----------|------------|------------|
| users | `user.model.js` | fullName, email, password, role, subscription, isOnline |
| doctors | `doctor.model.js` | userId, name, specialization, experience, consultationFee, availableSlots |
| appointments | `appointment.model.js` | patientId, doctorId, date, timeSlot, meetLink, attachedReportUrl |
| prescriptions | `prescription.model.js` | appointmentId, doctorId, patientId, diagnosis, medicines[], signature, verification |
| imagingreports | `imagingReport.model.js` | patientId, prediction, confidence, high_priority_findings[], risk_score, heatmapImage |
| clinicalreports | `clinicalReport.model.js` | patientId, doctorId, soap{}, status |
| medicines | `medicine.model.js` | name, price, category, stock, requiresPrescription |
| orders | `order.model.js` | patientId, items[], totalAmount, status, paymentMethod |
| labappointments | `labAppointment.model.js` | patientId, labTestId, date, status, reportStatus |
| labtests | `labTest.model.js` | Test metadata and pricing |
| labreports | `labReport.model.js` | Lab analysis results |
| labreferences | `labReference.model.js` | Reference ranges for lab values |
