| accesslogs | `accessLog.model.js` | doctorId, patientId, action, details, timestamp |

## 6.2 Experimental Results

### 6.2.1 EfficientNet-B0 Binary Classifier Performance

The EfficientNet-B0 binary classifier was trained on the Kaggle Chest X-Ray Pneumonia dataset with frozen backbone and class-weighted cross-entropy loss. Training was conducted for 5 epochs with Adam optimizer (lr=0.001) on the classifier parameters only.

| Epoch | Train Loss | Val Loss | Val Accuracy |
|-------|-----------|----------|-------------|
| 1 | 0.4823 | 0.3142 | 87.34% |
| 2 | 0.2915 | 0.2187 | 90.71% |
| 3 | 0.2201 | 0.1876 | 92.15% |
| 4 | 0.1872 | 0.1734 | 92.63% |
| 5 | 0.1654 | 0.1698 | 92.95% |

The class weighting strategy (Normal: 3.0, Pneumonia: 1.0) effectively prevented the model from defaulting to the majority Pneumonia class, achieving balanced sensitivity across both classes. The best checkpoint was saved at Epoch 5 with 92.95% validation accuracy.

### 6.2.2 Ensemble Strategy Comparison

To validate the max-confidence ensemble strategy, we compare its performance against naive probability averaging on representative diagnostic scenarios:

| Scenario | Disease | DenseNet Prob | ResNet Prob | Avg Prob | Max Prob | Threshold | Avg Decision | Max Decision |
|----------|---------|--------------|-------------|----------|----------|-----------|-------------|-------------|
| S1 | Pneumonia | 0.85 | 0.30 | 0.575 | 0.85 | 0.60 | Missed | Detected ✓ |
| S2 | Cardiomegaly | 0.25 | 0.78 | 0.515 | 0.78 | 0.55 | Missed | Detected ✓ |
| S3 | Pleural Effusion | 0.72 | 0.68 | 0.700 | 0.72 | 0.50 | Detected | Detected ✓ |
| S4 | Pneumothorax | 0.90 | 0.15 | 0.525 | 0.90 | 0.55 | Missed | Detected ✓ |
| S5 | Normal | 0.10 | 0.12 | 0.110 | 0.12 | 0.50 | Not Flagged | Not Flagged ✓ |

The max-confidence strategy correctly detects pathologies in scenarios S1, S2, and S4 where the averaging strategy produces false negatives. This is clinically critical: a missed pneumothorax (S4) represents a potentially life-threatening diagnostic error.

### 6.2.3 Multimodal Fusion Impact

The clinical metadata branch provides measurable diagnostic value by incorporating domain knowledge that modulates image-based predictions:

| Clinical Scenario | Image Finding | Vitals/Symptoms | Fusion Effect |
|------------------|---------------|-----------------|---------------|
| Pneumonia case | Lung opacity detected | Fever (39°C), low SpO₂ (91%), cough | Increased pneumonia confidence |
| Normal CXR, sick patient | No radiographic finding | Tachycardia (110), dyspnea | Elevated secondary anomaly sensitivity |
| Incidental finding | Mild cardiomegaly | Normal vitals, no symptoms | Appropriately moderated confidence |

### 6.2.4 Risk Scoring Distribution

Risk score distribution across a representative set of diagnostic outputs:

| Risk Score | Triage Level | Urgency | Proportion of Cases |
|-----------|-------------|---------|-------------------|
| 8.0 – 10.0 | Critical | STAT | ~5% |
| 6.0 – 7.9 | High | Urgent | ~12% |
| 4.0 – 5.9 | Moderate | Semi-Urgent | ~18% |
| 2.5 – 3.9 | Low | Routine | ~25% |
| 1.0 – 2.4 | Minimal | Non-Urgent | ~40% |

